article.headline: Wichita State 83, Panhandle State 55
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- P.J. Couisnard scored 18 points, seven in a key first-half run, and Paul Miller added 11 as Wichita State beat Panhandle State 83-55 Friday night. Couisnard had a layup, dunk, 3-pointer and two steals as Wichita State (1-0) opened the game with a 19-3 run. The Shockers extended their lead over the Division II Aggies to 35-11 with 6:00 left in the first half before Panhandle State (0-2) got its offense started. The Aggies closed within 49-36 on a 14-2 run that spanned the halves. William Preston had five of his 13 points in the opening 1:45 of the second half. But the Shockers responded with a 13-0 run over the next 7:33, and the Aggies never threatened again. Couisnard was perfect shooting for the night, hitting 5 of 5 from the field and 7 of 7 from the free throw line. He also had 11 rebounds to lead the Shockers. As a team, Wichita State outrebounded the Aggies 53-33, and the Shockers outscored the Aggies 38-12 in the paint and 22-6 on second-chance shots. Marquette transfer Karon Bradley was the third Shocker in scoring in double figures, finishing with 10. Juan Carson had 16 points and nine rebounds off the bench to lead the Aggies in both categories and Eddie Moss scored 11. Wichita State limited Oklahoma Panhandle State to 29.2 percent shooting. Matt Braeuer, returning from mononucleosis, had nine points.
